Christmas decorations, fireworks

45
00:06:50,022 --> 00:06:55,062
and presents for everyone.
Here, my friends!

46
00:06:56,222 --> 00:06:59,742
Names of the streets are
not too inventive either.

47
00:06:59,981 --> 00:07:03,381
What city doesn't have
a 1st Sadovaya or a 2nd Zagorodnaya,

48
00:07:03,622 --> 00:07:08,501
a 3rd Factory St., a Park St.,
an Industrial St.,

49
00:07:08,741 --> 00:07:12,780
or a 3rd Constructors St.?
Sounds romantic, doesn't it?

50
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,300
Staircases that all look the same

51
00:07:15,541 --> 00:07:17,940
are all painted with a standard
pleasant color.

52
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:21,820
Standard apartments furnished
with standard furniture,

53
00:07:22,061 --> 00:07:26,060
standard locks cut into
blind featureless doors.

54
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:32,619
Zhenya, darling,
I have an unusual proposition.

55
00:07:32,859 --> 00:07:34,179
Oh, is that so?

56
00:07:35,219 --> 00:07:36,539
I'm scared already.

57
00:07:37,779 --> 00:07:41,579
Zhenya, let's see
in the New Year together.

58
00:07:42,779 --> 00:07:47,218
Well of course.
Isn't that how we planned it?

59
00:07:47,458 --> 00:07:48,658
No.

60
00:07:48,899 --> 00:07:52,058
You don't understand.
Let it be just you and me.

61
00:07:52,298 --> 00:07:54,458
What do you mean "just you and me"?
I don't understand.

62
00:07:55,138 --> 00:07:56,737
Let's not go to the Katanyans.

63
00:07:57,378 --> 00:08:02,017
But that's impossible, Galya.
We've already made arrangements.

64
00:08:02,777 --> 00:08:07,737
They are my friends.
And you've already made your crab salad.

65
00:08:07,977 --> 00:08:10,097
You know I love crabs!

66
00:08:10,697 --> 00:08:13,096
That's great.
We'll eat them together.

67
00:08:13,696 --> 00:08:15,857
Where will we eat them?

68
00:08:17,096 --> 00:08:19,097
You are so slow!

69
00:08:19,336 --> 00:08:21,776
We will stay here, at your place.

70
00:08:22,016 --> 00:08:24,376
Right here?

71
00:08:25,856 --> 00:08:27,616
But what about the Katanyans?

72
00:08:27,856 --> 00:08:30,335
Oleg invites me to celebrate

73
00:08:30,576 --> 00:08:32,855
at the Ostankino TV
tower restaurant.

74
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:34,775
Give me the top.

75
00:08:35,535 --> 00:08:37,415
- It rotates.
- Who?

76
00:08:37,655 --> 00:08:39,135
The restaurant.

77
00:08:40,695 --> 00:08:45,814
Well if you want to rotate,
then please do.

78
00:08:46,974 --> 00:08:49,654
I want to see in the
New Year with you.

79
00:08:51,454 --> 00:08:54,134
Really? Let's do it then!

80
00:08:56,974 --> 00:08:59,213
- You are so stupid!
- And who else shall we invite?

81
00:08:59,454 --> 00:09:01,773
That's the point. No one.

82
00:09:02,213 --> 00:09:07,173
What do you mean, no one?
And what about my mother?

83
00:09:08,213 --> 00:09:10,813
Your mother will go someplace.
She'll cook everything,

84
00:09:11,053 --> 00:09:15,172
lay the table, I'll help her.
You got a terrific mom.

85
00:09:16,693 --> 00:09:20,732
Wonderful idea! How come
I didn't think about it myself?

86
00:09:20,973 --> 00:09:23,972
One of the two has to be more
clever than the other.

87
00:09:24,212 --> 00:09:27,252
- It will be you.
- Zhenya, stop it!

88
00:09:27,492 --> 00:09:30,052
And what about the Katanyans?
I don't understand...

89
00:09:31,811 --> 00:09:34,812
Oleg invited me to see
in the New Year

90
00:09:35,051 --> 00:09:36,651
at a monastery in Suzdal.

91
00:09:36,891 --> 00:09:39,771
To hell with Oleg!
To hell with the monastery!

92
00:09:40,651 --> 00:09:44,531
I don't want to go anywhere.
I want to be with you.

93
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:47,290
With me?

94
00:09:59,809 --> 00:10:03,329
Excuse me, I'm looking
for the 3rd Constructors St.

95
00:10:03,570 --> 00:10:06,809
It's over there,
behind those tall buildings.

96
00:10:07,049 --> 00:10:09,849
- You'll see a church there.
- Thank you.

97
00:10:15,248 --> 00:10:18,968
We will see in the New Year together.
Just you and me.

98
00:10:19,969 --> 00:10:21,448
I'll have one too many...

99
00:10:23,968 --> 00:10:27,568
and become brave and bold...

100
00:10:28,408 --> 00:10:31,608
And I'll finally tell you
everything I have to tell you.

101
00:10:31,848 --> 00:10:33,168
Znenya!

102
00:10:34,648 --> 00:10:38,968
I don't believe it!
Are you going to propose?

103
00:10:39,887 --> 00:10:42,287
After two years of being together...

104
00:10:47,526 --> 00:10:51,806
Let's wait until New Year's eve,
when the bells chime...

105
00:10:52,046 --> 00:10:54,046
Let's wait...

106
00:10:55,966 --> 00:11:00,326
It's just that I'm afraid
you will never summon your courage.

107
00:11:00,645 --> 00:11:06,605
It is the cowardice...
of an old bachelor.

108
00:11:07,566 --> 00:11:11,725
You know,
I already proposed to a woman once.

109
00:11:11,965 --> 00:11:15,685
To my utter amazement
she said "yes".

110
00:11:16,444 --> 00:11:18,445
But when I imagined,

111
00:11:18,684 --> 00:11:21,164
that she will come
to live at my place,

112
00:11:23,204 --> 00:11:25,164
and every day...

113
00:11:26,404 --> 00:11:29,204
she will flash before my eyes...

114
00:11:30,764 --> 00:11:32,764
hither and thither,
hither and thither...

115
00:11:33,363 --> 00:11:36,323
I broke down and ran
away to Leningrad.

116
00:11:39,363 --> 00:11:41,803
Will you run away from me too?

117
00:11:42,683 --> 00:11:45,643
It's impossible to run away from you.

118
00:11:48,363 --> 00:11:51,362
My decision is final an irreversible.

119
00:11:52,523 --> 00:11:56,562
I held on for a long
time and finally broke.

120
00:11:59,082 --> 00:12:00,322
Zhenya...

121
00:12:02,962 --> 00:12:07,361
What do you think,
when do people sing?

122
00:12:08,801 --> 00:12:10,041
Sing?

123
00:12:10,961 --> 00:12:13,521
When? At street rallies.

124
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:16,720
- Well... Any other time?
- They sing in the opera.

125
00:12:17,441 --> 00:12:19,281
They sing when they
have one too many.

126
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:21,841
Stupid! You know when people sing?

127
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:25,440
- When they don't have
a musical ear? - No.

128
00:12:25,681 --> 00:12:29,440
- When they're happy.
- That's right.

129
00:12:44,359 --> 00:12:47,439
There will be no one in the house,

130
00:12:48,438 --> 00:12:50,399
Just the twilight,

131
00:12:51,078 --> 00:12:53,519
Just one winter day

132
00:12:53,758 --> 00:12:59,398
In the opening of the curtains,
Someone forgot to shut,

133
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:02,838
Curtains, someone forgot to shut.

134
00:13:07,678 --> 00:13:11,037
Just damp white snow lumps

135
00:13:12,037 --> 00:13:15,357
Swiftly flying by.

136
00:13:15,676 --> 00:13:20,436
There's just the roofs and
the snow, and...

137
00:13:20,676 --> 00:13:23,236
Just the roofs and the snow,
And no one else,

138
00:13:23,476 --> 00:13:26,557
There's no one else.

139
00:13:28,956 --> 00:13:32,236
And once again the hoarfrost
Will draw its tracery,

140
00:13:33,276 --> 00:13:35,796
And like before I will be
caught in the whirlwind

141
00:13:36,035 --> 00:13:41,675
Of last year's despondency,
and the memories of another witer,

142
00:13:44,115 --> 00:13:46,515
And the memories of another Winter.

143
00:13:47,755 --> 00:13:53,075
But suddenly the curtain shudder
with someone's intrusion.

144
00:13:53,394 --> 00:13:57,114
Measuring the silence with
your soft steps,

145
00:13:57,355 --> 00:14:03,234
Measuring the silence,
you will appear like the future itself.

146
00:14:04,674 --> 00:14:07,433
You will be standing in the doorway,

147
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:12,193
Dressed in something
white and simple,

148
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:16,392
Like one of those fabrics,

149
00:14:16,953 --> 00:14:19,512
Out of which they make snow flakes,

150
00:14:20,353 --> 00:14:22,912
Out of which they make snow flakes.

151
00:14:23,753 --> 00:14:26,673
There will be no one in the house,

152
00:14:27,952 --> 00:14:30,192
Just the twilight.

153
00:14:32,432 --> 00:14:35,551
Just one winter day in the opening

154
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:38,871
Of the curtains,
someone forgot to shut,

155
00:14:39,192 --> 00:14:41,831
Curtains, someone forgot to shut.

156
00:15:17,669 --> 00:15:19,549
- Maria Dmitrievna...
- Quiet!

157
00:15:20,508 --> 00:15:21,708
Happy New Year!

158
00:15:21,949 --> 00:15:23,229
Not so loud, will you!

159
00:15:23,668 --> 00:15:24,668
Why?

160
00:15:24,948 --> 00:15:29,428
- Who is it, mother?
- It's just a neighbor, dear.

161
00:15:29,668 --> 00:15:33,468
- What's going on?
- Pavel, come back tomorrow.

162
00:15:34,188 --> 00:15:36,147
I'm leaving for Leningrad tonight.

163
00:15:36,948 --> 00:15:38,387
Well, bon voyage.

164
00:15:52,946 --> 00:15:54,626
What do you think you're doing?

165
00:15:54,866 --> 00:16:00,266
- Mother, who is it again?
- A telegram from aunt Vera.

166
00:16:00,746 --> 00:16:03,666
Remember how you taught us boys
to always tell

167
00:16:03,906 --> 00:16:04,986
the truth?

168
00:16:05,226 --> 00:16:08,666
There are situations
when it's better to tell a lye.

169
00:16:08,905 --> 00:16:11,786
But Misha and Sasha
are waiting for us at the bathhouse.

170
00:16:12,025 --> 00:16:13,025
That's no problem.

171
00:16:13,265 --> 00:16:15,345
I'm leaving to Leningrad right after.

172
00:16:15,585 --> 00:16:19,065
Why do you have to go to
Leningrad?

173
00:16:19,305 --> 00:16:21,945
Irina is there on business,
and I'm flying over

174
00:16:22,185 --> 00:16:25,224
to see in the New Year with her.
What's going on anyway?

175
00:16:26,665 --> 00:16:30,104
- It's a secret.
- What secret?

176
00:16:30,344 --> 00:16:35,264
- You'll find out in due time.
- Zhenya has no secrets from me.

177
00:16:35,504 --> 00:16:37,303
Go on, split!

178
00:16:49,423 --> 00:16:54,503
Zhenya, I have to go.
I have so much to do!

179
00:17:01,342 --> 00:17:02,822
- Galya!..
- What?

180
00:17:07,101 --> 00:17:08,342
Galya...

181
00:17:11,182 --> 00:17:12,981
The thing is...

182
00:17:16,021 --> 00:17:18,181
How do they say that?..

183
00:17:20,780 --> 00:17:22,260
I love you.

184
00:17:24,780 --> 00:17:26,900
I want you to marry me.

185
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:33,340
But I will always be flashing before
your eyes.

186
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:36,859
Please do.

187
00:17:38,499 --> 00:17:40,500
I want you to.

188
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:50,579
Here's the key.
Come at 11 to see in the New Year.

189
00:17:59,418 --> 00:18:00,978
Shall I bring the salad?

190
00:18:01,938 --> 00:18:03,217
The salad?

191
00:18:04,418 --> 00:18:07,418
I didn't understand the main thing:
do you say "yes"?

192
00:18:08,658 --> 00:18:10,657
I took the key, didn't I?

193
00:18:12,537 --> 00:18:14,377
And what does that mean?

194
00:18:16,937 --> 00:18:18,937
That doesn't mean anything.

195
00:18:23,177 --> 00:18:27,096
See you tonight.
Say good-bye to your mother from me.

196
00:18:31,696 --> 00:18:35,136
- I'm worried about the Katanyans.
- Forget it.

197
00:19:04,814 --> 00:19:06,054
Mother!

198
00:19:08,174 --> 00:19:12,093
Amidst a bustling ball,

199
00:19:13,654 --> 00:19:15,574
Suddenly...

200
00:19:17,813 --> 00:19:21,253
In the troubles
of the mundane bustle...

201
00:19:23,692 --> 00:19:28,012
- I think I'm getting married.
- I think so too.

202
00:19:28,452 --> 00:19:30,772
What do you think of Galya?

203
00:19:31,012 --> 00:19:33,252
You're the one
who's getting married, not me.

204
00:19:34,652 --> 00:19:36,652
But you are my mother!

205
00:19:37,571 --> 00:19:42,652
I hope you won't forget it
after you get married.

206
00:19:45,171 --> 00:19:48,331
I take it that you don't like her.

207
00:19:48,571 --> 00:19:51,570
Well, I'm not particularly
mad about her,

208
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:56,410
But she's rather intelligent
and has good manners.

209
00:19:56,651 --> 00:19:57,650
I see.

210
00:19:57,890 --> 00:20:01,810
If you don't get married now,
you'll never get married.

211
00:20:02,050 --> 00:20:04,050
I'm already 36...

212
00:20:04,330 --> 00:20:08,529
It's not very polite
to remind me of my age.

213
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:11,809
Even though I take no offense.

214
00:20:12,849 --> 00:20:13,849
Get up!

215
00:20:14,650 --> 00:20:18,169
Stop it! I'm not offended.
I'm a terrific mom, remember?

216
00:20:18,409 --> 00:20:21,569
I'll cook everything
and go visit a friend.

217
00:20:22,929 --> 00:20:26,928
- Where are the goblets?
- I'll find them. Goblets!

218
00:20:27,489 --> 00:20:28,848
They should be here.

219
00:20:29,089 --> 00:20:31,568
Moving from one place to another,
you can't find a thing.

220
00:20:31,808 --> 00:20:33,368
They're not here.

221
00:20:35,008 --> 00:20:36,488
There they are!

222
00:20:38,808 --> 00:20:41,807
I wonder what she saw in me?

223
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,568
She's much younger than I am.

224
00:20:45,727 --> 00:20:47,887
And then, she's so beautiful!

225
00:20:48,647 --> 00:20:52,807
I'm also surprised,
she chose such a dimwit.

226
00:20:53,087 --> 00:20:54,086
Dimwit?

227
00:20:55,647 --> 00:20:58,646
Did you have to tell her
about Leningrad?

228
00:20:59,566 --> 00:21:02,566
When a man proposes to one woman,

229
00:21:02,806 --> 00:21:05,006
he doesn't talk about another.

230
00:21:05,606 --> 00:21:08,606
- Oh really? I didn't know.
- Yes.

231
00:21:08,846 --> 00:21:10,845
Now I know everything!

232
00:21:11,605 --> 00:21:14,925
Now I know how a man should propose.

233
00:21:15,165 --> 00:21:16,405
You windbag!

234
00:21:17,925 --> 00:21:20,525
- Who rang the doorbell all the time?
- Pavel.

235
00:21:20,765 --> 00:21:24,564
He's leaving for Leningrad.
I told him to go away.

236
00:21:24,925 --> 00:21:28,604
Maybe I could go
to the bathhouse anyway?

237
00:21:28,925 --> 00:21:30,924
It won't do you any harm,

238
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:33,924
If you will see
in the New Year clean.

239
00:21:34,164 --> 00:21:35,684
It's decided. I'll go take a bath.

240
00:21:36,244 --> 00:21:41,604
A bath in every apartment -
that's the way it should be.

241
00:21:42,563 --> 00:21:44,404
This is civilization.

242
00:21:44,643 --> 00:21:46,923
- Are you talking to me?
- Yes.

243
00:21:47,403 --> 00:21:49,163
But the process of washing yourself,

244
00:21:49,403 --> 00:21:53,363
that in a bathhouse acquires
the meaning of a ceremonial ritual,

245
00:21:55,082 --> 00:21:58,082
In your bath at home
is just scraping off the dirt.

246
00:21:59,163 --> 00:22:02,962
And then this Russian tradition
of wishing "A light steam".

247
00:22:07,161 --> 00:22:08,362
Here's a refill.

248
00:22:08,602 --> 00:22:10,602
Did you ever see steam
in your bathroom at home?

249
00:22:11,481 --> 00:22:13,481
Misha is right, a good bath
makes you clean, body and soul.

250
00:22:15,921 --> 00:22:17,401
Guys!

251
00:22:19,441 --> 00:22:22,760
It's great here, but I have to go.

252
00:22:23,161 --> 00:22:25,841
No, you won't get away with that.

253
00:22:26,081 --> 00:22:27,721
We're all waiting.

254
00:22:28,481 --> 00:22:29,961
What are you waiting for?

255
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:34,800
Aren't we gonna drink to your
engagement?

256
00:22:36,479 --> 00:22:37,680
Here, in the bathhouse?

257
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:41,639
Zhenya is right.
They don't serve alcohol in a bathhouse.

258
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,920
If not for me,
the situation would be hopeless.

259
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:50,399
There you go!

260
00:22:51,798 --> 00:22:53,799
No, no, I can't.

261
00:22:54,839 --> 00:22:59,038
Just one shot.
I have to go to the airport.

262
00:22:59,559 --> 00:23:01,558
No sweat, guys!

263
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,518
Everyone has to be in shape.

264
00:23:06,237 --> 00:23:10,077
Why don't we do it tomorrow!
At my place.

265
00:23:10,318 --> 00:23:13,477
I'll introduce you to my wife.

266
00:23:13,718 --> 00:23:16,037
Tomorrow I will be in Leningrad.

267
00:23:16,277 --> 00:23:17,718
Go ahead, drink.

268
00:23:19,517 --> 00:23:22,077
I wonder what you chose.

269
00:23:22,316 --> 00:23:25,317
Not "what", but "who"!

270
00:23:26,717 --> 00:23:29,716
That's terrible: Vodka after beer.

271
00:23:29,996 --> 00:23:32,036
I'm just off a night shift...

272
00:23:33,476 --> 00:23:36,636
There, here's a chocolate bar.
Something to chase it down with.

273
00:23:36,876 --> 00:23:39,396
All right, just one shot.

274
00:23:39,916 --> 00:23:41,996
Pavel, your toast.

275
00:23:43,316 --> 00:23:45,595
You are the most eloquent of us.

276
00:23:46,235 --> 00:23:49,915
- And you - the least intelligent.
- Thank you.

277
00:23:50,155 --> 00:23:51,435
Here's a oast...

278
00:23:51,675 --> 00:23:55,354
To Zhenya Lukashin.

279
00:23:55,595 --> 00:23:56,915
No, seriously.

280
00:23:57,155 --> 00:23:59,154
The most bashful one of us,

281
00:23:59,395 --> 00:24:03,594
who finally overcame his shyness
and decided to get married.

282
00:24:03,994 --> 00:24:06,474
The last one of us.

283
00:24:06,994 --> 00:24:10,673
Zhenya, now the serious part.
Be happy!

284
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:14,914
- Be happy, Zhenya.
- This calls for a drink.

285
00:24:15,153 --> 00:24:16,913
This is serious.

286
00:24:23,632 --> 00:24:27,312
Listen, what's her name?

287
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:36,872
She has a beautiful name.

288
00:24:39,152 --> 00:24:40,392
Galya.

289
00:24:40,711 --> 00:24:43,511
And what's more, an uncommon one.

290
00:24:43,752 --> 00:24:47,751
Guys, we have no choice.

291
00:24:49,231 --> 00:24:50,511
Here's to Galya!

292
00:24:52,231 --> 00:24:53,871
To Galya bottoms up!

293
00:24:54,911 --> 00:24:57,631
Galya, be happy!

294
00:24:57,870 --> 00:25:00,431
You bastards!

295
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:04,750
I had a night shift...

296
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:07,389
Not cold enough!

297
00:25:08,910 --> 00:25:10,910
Tell us how you met.

298
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:13,589
It's a long story.

299
00:25:14,909 --> 00:25:16,909
She came to my outpatients clinic.

300
00:25:17,149 --> 00:25:19,069
Is she sick?

301
00:25:19,310 --> 00:25:20,549
No.

302
00:25:22,469 --> 00:25:24,189
She had a dislocation.

303
00:25:24,429 --> 00:25:27,949
A kink! Well that explains
why she is marrying you.

304
00:25:28,788 --> 00:25:31,788
Let's drink to them both
being healthy.

305
00:25:32,028 --> 00:25:35,548
Where do you get those bottles from?
Put it away!

306
00:25:35,788 --> 00:25:37,788
My wife asked me
to buy some for tonight.

307
00:25:38,028 --> 00:25:41,508
If we go on at such pace,

308
00:25:41,747 --> 00:25:43,748
I have good chances
of missing my plane.

309
00:25:43,987 --> 00:25:48,627
Pavel, trust me. I never get drunk.

310
00:25:48,867 --> 00:25:50,347
Give me your ticket.

311
00:25:50,587 --> 00:25:53,427
It's definitely bad for my health!

312
00:25:54,387 --> 00:25:57,386
She'll think I'm an alcoholic!

313
00:26:00,587 --> 00:26:03,827
That's unheard of!
A doctor refuses to drink to good health.

314
00:26:04,906 --> 00:26:09,226
Why did I have to come here!

315
00:26:13,506 --> 00:26:16,786
Now tell us how you met her.

316
00:26:18,905 --> 00:26:21,105
Are you asking me? Who with?

317
00:26:22,305 --> 00:26:24,505
Galya. Or is there someone else?

318
00:26:24,745 --> 00:26:27,345
No, there's no one. I'm single.

319
00:26:29,585 --> 00:26:32,064
- What to?
- Let's drink to bachelors.

320
00:26:32,304 --> 00:26:34,304
To unmarried life! Hip-hip-hurrah!

321
00:26:34,904 --> 00:26:36,904
You can't miss this one!

322
00:26:37,144 --> 00:26:38,623
It's all the same to you!

323
00:26:39,744 --> 00:26:43,223
But I can't imagine
what's going to happen to me,

324
00:26:43,464 --> 00:26:46,623
if I maybe come home in time
to see in the New Year.

325
00:26:47,383 --> 00:26:52,423
People, I have a very
important toast.

326
00:26:52,983 --> 00:26:55,503
You've had enough.
You're getting married, remember?

327
00:26:56,303 --> 00:26:57,703
I haven't forgotten.

328
00:26:57,942 --> 00:27:00,622
If you do, I will remind you.

329
00:27:01,143 --> 00:27:04,862
Guys, let's drink to our friendship.

330
00:27:05,143 --> 00:27:06,902
That's a good boy!

331
00:27:07,142 --> 00:27:10,822
Good speech!
You're a natural born orator.

332
00:27:11,061 --> 00:27:12,541
Give me some space.

333
00:27:12,902 --> 00:27:16,981
Let's weigh ourselves "Brudershaft".

334
00:27:22,141 --> 00:27:25,141
What will the two of us
weigh together?

335
00:27:26,501 --> 00:27:30,260
Guys, I have a lyrical
romantic toast.

336
00:27:30,901 --> 00:27:34,660
That's enough!
We have to go to the airport.

337
00:27:34,901 --> 00:27:38,500
- What for?
- One of us is going to Leningrad.

338
00:27:38,740 --> 00:27:44,539
- Let's go!
- Let's fly!

339
00:27:44,780 --> 00:27:48,419
Fasten your bed-sheets!
Prepare for takeoff!

340
00:27:49,139 --> 00:27:55,059
Down below, under the wing sings

341
00:27:56,179 --> 00:27:59,179
the green see of the Taiga.

342
00:28:02,459 --> 00:28:06,459
Down below, under the wing sings

343
00:28:09,898 --> 00:28:13,818
the green see of the Taiga.

344
00:28:16,618 --> 00:28:21,017
Attention all passengers,
boarding TU-134,

345
00:28:21,377 --> 00:28:26,017
flight 392,
en route from Moscow to Leningrad.

346
00:28:26,897 --> 00:28:30,096
All passengers please proceed
to the departure gate.

347
00:28:34,176 --> 00:28:37,576
- I think that's our flight.
- I think you're right.

348
00:28:38,896 --> 00:28:41,736
Do you remember,
which one of us is flying?

349
00:28:41,976 --> 00:28:42,976
No.

350
00:28:44,896 --> 00:28:47,696
Wait, trust me.

351
00:28:49,215 --> 00:28:53,375
- Let's appeal to common logic.
- Let's.

352
00:28:55,135 --> 00:28:58,374
- Are you flying to Leningrad?
- No.

353
00:28:58,615 --> 00:29:00,255
Me neither.

354
00:29:01,575 --> 00:29:05,855
Flight No 392 to Leningrad
boarding now.

355
00:29:07,374 --> 00:29:09,814
Can Pavel be flying to Leningrad?

356
00:29:11,894 --> 00:29:12,894
He can.

357
00:29:13,614 --> 00:29:15,453
What about Zhenya?

358
00:29:18,893 --> 00:29:20,333
He can too.

359
00:29:21,893 --> 00:29:23,413
They both can.

360
00:29:28,373 --> 00:29:29,573
Shall we cast lots?

361
00:29:33,612 --> 00:29:36,252
Let's not give ourselves
into the hands of chance.

362
00:29:39,452 --> 00:29:41,332
When in the bathhouse,
what did we drink to?

363
00:29:42,571 --> 00:29:44,532
Lukashin's health.

364
00:29:44,971 --> 00:29:47,731
Because he's getting married.

365
00:29:48,892 --> 00:29:52,811
- You've got an amazing memory.
- Later.

366
00:29:54,371 --> 00:29:58,451
That means,
Zhenya is flying to Leningrad,

367
00:29:59,891 --> 00:30:02,011
to attend his own wedding.

368
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:07,730
And he would say so himself,
if he wasn't that tired.

369
00:30:07,970 --> 00:30:09,370
Wait!

370
00:30:11,050 --> 00:30:14,530
He said he met his fiancee
at his outpatient clinic,

371
00:30:14,770 --> 00:30:17,010
when she came to see a doctor.

372
00:30:17,249 --> 00:30:18,729
I will answer you.

373
00:30:20,209 --> 00:30:21,689
What does that mean?

374
00:30:23,129 --> 00:30:27,088
Than means, she was in Moscow on
a business trip.

375
00:30:29,608 --> 00:30:31,609
Iron logic.

376
00:30:32,209 --> 00:30:35,208
Boarding Aeroflot flight 392

377
00:30:35,449 --> 00:30:39,449
en route from Moscow to Leningrad
completed.

378
00:30:41,128 --> 00:30:42,368
Careful!

379
00:30:42,608 --> 00:30:46,727
- Where are you taking me?
- To meet your happiness.

380
00:30:48,447 --> 00:30:51,727
Wait! It's a good thing
we washed him.

381
00:31:40,004 --> 00:31:42,884
Attention! Flight

382
00:31:43,124 --> 00:31:45,924
392 from Moscow has just landed.

383
00:31:46,164 --> 00:31:50,563
- Careful!
- What did I do to deserve this?

384
00:31:50,803 --> 00:31:55,283
Flight from Moscow has just landed.

385
00:31:56,603 --> 00:31:57,843
I'm cold!

386
00:32:09,522 --> 00:32:10,762
Damn!

387
00:32:14,521 --> 00:32:16,362
You shouldn't drink so much.

388
00:32:18,681 --> 00:32:19,922
Pavel!

389
00:32:20,441 --> 00:32:25,122
Attention all passengers
flying to Krasnoyarsk.

390
00:32:25,361 --> 00:32:28,361
Your flight is delayed until 12 p.m.

391
00:32:28,601 --> 00:32:32,161
due to bad weather in Krasnoyarsk.

392
00:32:38,521 --> 00:32:40,360
What time is it?

393
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:44,120
2 hours 50 minutes to go until the
New Year.

394
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,360
Watch yourself, young man!

395
00:32:50,999 --> 00:32:53,759
- Where am I?
- Same place I am.

396
00:32:55,959 --> 00:32:58,439
- And where are you?
- At the airport.

397
00:32:59,599 --> 00:33:02,598
It's bad weather in Krasnoyarsk.

398
00:33:03,439 --> 00:33:09,398
At worst I'll see in the New Year
in this armchair...

399
00:33:11,598 --> 00:33:13,598
And at best?

400
00:33:14,478 --> 00:33:17,357
Also in an armchair, only in the air.

401
00:33:17,878 --> 00:33:20,277
Have you ever seen in
the New Year in the air?

402
00:33:20,518 --> 00:33:22,957
No. And I don't want to.

403
00:33:23,198 --> 00:33:25,117
Me either. But what can I do?

404
00:33:25,357 --> 00:33:28,757
- Who are you?
- I'm a human being.

405
00:33:33,516 --> 00:33:36,796
We saw Pavel to the airport,
and now I'm going home.

406
00:33:37,037 --> 00:33:39,356
Very well, all the best.

407
00:33:40,356 --> 00:33:42,596
- Happy New Year.
- Same to you.

408
00:33:45,116 --> 00:33:47,715
Drop the familiarities.

409
00:33:51,596 --> 00:33:53,676
Don't you think it's too early,
young man?

410
00:33:56,115 --> 00:33:57,595
You free?

411
00:33:57,835 --> 00:34:00,835
- Yes. Where to?
- 3rd Constructors St.,

412
00:34:01,075 --> 00:34:04,115
25, apartment 12, 4th floor.

413
00:34:04,674 --> 00:34:06,235
I don't care if it's the 5th!

414
00:34:43,072 --> 00:34:44,312
Taxi!

415
00:34:46,112 --> 00:34:48,111
Let me out of here!

416
00:34:52,431 --> 00:34:55,431
People! Happy New Year!

417
00:35:01,670 --> 00:35:03,910
Home at last!

418
00:35:04,510 --> 00:35:05,830
I'm home.

419
00:35:07,870 --> 00:35:12,510
"There will be no one in he
house..."

420
00:35:13,190 --> 00:35:18,629
And who are these people here?
You're not afraid of me?

421
00:35:18,949 --> 00:35:20,630
Careful!

422
00:35:20,869 --> 00:35:22,870
I fell through. Thank you.

423
00:35:23,590 --> 00:35:26,709
Go ahead... Only after you...

424
00:35:28,109 --> 00:35:30,069
You won't bite me, will you?

425
00:35:33,189 --> 00:35:35,268
Going up.

426
00:35:35,509 --> 00:35:39,388
Come visit me. It's apartment 12.

427
00:35:39,669 --> 00:35:44,987
"Jim, give me your paw for
happiness". - Come on.

428
00:35:45,508 --> 00:35:46,748
He doesn't want to!

429
00:35:47,347 --> 00:35:49,508
Happy New Year to you!

430
00:35:53,747 --> 00:35:55,187
Dogs walking around!

431
00:36:07,106 --> 00:36:08,547
Mother!

432
00:37:16,342 --> 00:37:18,222
Careful, careful...

433
00:37:53,180 --> 00:37:54,899
Hold the elevator, please!

434
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:23,370
Hey!..

435
00:40:38,608 --> 00:40:40,169
Wake up! Do you hear me?

436
00:40:41,489 --> 00:40:44,128
Wake up this very minute! Get up!

437
00:40:45,328 --> 00:40:46,448
Are you dead or alive?

438
00:40:49,848 --> 00:40:51,248
All right!..

439
00:40:53,008 --> 00:40:55,847
Wake up now! Do you hear me?

440
00:40:56,088 --> 00:40:58,168
Get up! What are you doing here?

441
00:41:02,247 --> 00:41:04,647
Don't jolt me!

442
00:41:06,326 --> 00:41:09,167
I want to get some sleep.

443
00:41:11,326 --> 00:41:13,647
Who are you? How did you get here?

444
00:41:13,886 --> 00:41:17,566
Stop jolting me! Get up!

445
00:41:19,086 --> 00:41:22,446
- You're hurting me!
- Get up this very minute!

446
00:41:22,726 --> 00:41:25,566
Stop disturbing me!

447
00:41:25,805 --> 00:41:27,005
Unbelievable!

448
00:41:27,245 --> 00:41:29,685
All right, you asked for it!

449
00:41:56,923 --> 00:41:59,723
I warn you for the last time.

450
00:42:04,163 --> 00:42:08,403
Oh, that feels good!
Can I have some more?

451
00:42:11,002 --> 00:42:12,723
I'm sailing away!

452
00:42:16,162 --> 00:42:17,722
What is this?

453
00:42:22,762 --> 00:42:27,042
What are you doing? It's wet!
Are you crazy?

454
00:42:27,721 --> 00:42:30,241
Have you all gone mad?

455
00:42:30,641 --> 00:42:34,201
I'm not a flower-bed.

456
00:42:40,121 --> 00:42:41,960
Who are you?

457
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,640
What's going on here?

458
00:42:45,560 --> 00:42:48,000
Get out of here now!

459
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:50,880
This is unheard of!

460
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:53,759
- What are you doing here?
- I was sleeping.

461
00:42:55,239 --> 00:42:58,000
What? What do you want?

462
00:42:58,280 --> 00:43:00,679
Stop playing the fool!

463
00:43:01,079 --> 00:43:03,279
- Why?
- What are you doing lying here?

464
00:43:03,839 --> 00:43:05,879
Get out this instant!

465
00:43:06,118 --> 00:43:07,359
Now!

466
00:43:07,839 --> 00:43:12,559
What a boor! It's not enough
that you broke into my flat,

467
00:43:12,798 --> 00:43:15,798
but you behave like a gangster!

468
00:43:16,838 --> 00:43:17,998
What is this?

469
00:43:18,238 --> 00:43:21,757
- Your flat?
- That's right, I live here.

470
00:43:21,998 --> 00:43:24,997
- Then where do you suppose I live?
- I don't know.

471
00:43:25,238 --> 00:43:28,358
And I don't care. That's outrageous!

472
00:43:28,597 --> 00:43:32,557
For your information my fiancee
will be coming any minute now.

473
00:43:32,797 --> 00:43:33,797
I don't want her

474
00:43:34,037 --> 00:43:36,397
to see you here.

475
00:43:37,917 --> 00:43:40,997
How come your fiancee
will be coming to my place?

476
00:43:41,917 --> 00:43:47,836
It's a bad time for jokes!
My head's splitting!

477
00:43:49,556 --> 00:43:50,996
What time is it?

478
00:43:54,635 --> 00:43:56,875
My god, it's nearly 11 p.m.!
I'm expecting guests.

479
00:43:57,115 --> 00:44:01,475
And you presence
here is not at all welcome.

480
00:44:01,915 --> 00:44:06,035
How come your friends
will be coming to my place?

481
00:44:06,275 --> 00:44:07,995
I'm thirsty!

482
00:44:09,315 --> 00:44:14,315
Are you crazy? W
hy do you behave so outrageously?

483
00:44:14,554 --> 00:44:15,795
Listen to me!

484
00:44:16,034 --> 00:44:19,234
Get a hold of yourself.
Where do you think you are?

485
00:44:19,714 --> 00:44:23,554
At home. 25, 3rd Constructors St...

486
00:44:23,793 --> 00:44:24,993
Oh no!

487
00:44:25,234 --> 00:44:27,393
I live at 25, 3rd Constructor St.,

488
00:44:27,633 --> 00:44:28,634
Apartment 12.

489
00:44:28,873 --> 00:44:29,913
Oh no, darling.

490
00:44:30,153 --> 00:44:31,473
Shoo!

491
00:44:31,713 --> 00:44:34,553
Stop being a nuisance!

492
00:44:34,793 --> 00:44:38,753
I live here with my mother.
32 meters of space.

493
00:44:38,992 --> 00:44:43,193
No, me and my mother occupy
these 32 meters of space.

494
00:44:43,432 --> 00:44:47,152
Congratulations!
Can't say we have very big apartments.

495
00:44:47,392 --> 00:44:49,392
Very sharp observation.

496
00:44:49,632 --> 00:44:51,032
Who wrapped me
in this thing anyway?

497
00:44:51,272 --> 00:44:53,992
I will be much obliged,

498
00:44:54,232 --> 00:44:57,151
if you would evaporate
this very minute.

499
00:44:57,392 --> 00:45:02,271
Don't jolt me around!
I want some respect!

500
00:45:02,832 --> 00:45:03,872
Mother!

501
00:45:04,351 --> 00:45:05,351
Mother left.

502
00:45:05,791 --> 00:45:06,791
I'll kill you!

503
00:45:09,070 --> 00:45:12,831
- Whose mother left?
- Thank god, we have different mothers.

504
00:45:13,070 --> 00:45:14,151
Really?

505
00:45:23,990 --> 00:45:27,909
Pardon me... And both mothers left?

506
00:45:29,389 --> 00:45:32,429
I have a feeling, one of us is nuts.

507
00:45:34,149 --> 00:45:36,229
I know which one it is.

508
00:45:36,469 --> 00:45:38,149
Yes, me too.

509
00:45:38,828 --> 00:45:40,908
Are you hinting at me?

510
00:45:45,709 --> 00:45:46,988
Madhouse!

511
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:52,748
Why did you move my cupboard?

