situation over and done with.

766
01:08:27,058 --> 01:08:29,059
What do you think?

767
01:08:31,218 --> 01:08:33,858
I think it is a wonderful idea.

768
01:08:35,378 --> 01:08:39,738
Only on one condition:
that you will not be jealous of me.

769
01:08:41,337 --> 01:08:46,497
You see, I'm not that young
anymore, and I feel...

770
01:08:49,617 --> 01:08:50,617
Who is that?

771
01:08:52,617 --> 01:08:54,777
I haven't the slightest idea.

772
01:08:55,057 --> 01:08:56,737
Excuse me!

773
01:08:57,536 --> 01:08:58,777
I beg your pardon.

774
01:09:08,575 --> 01:09:12,855
I'm sorry, I wouldn't dream
of using my own key.

775
01:09:14,136 --> 01:09:16,376
What is it you want now?

776
01:09:16,615 --> 01:09:18,695
You see, it so happens...

777
01:09:18,935 --> 01:09:21,935
I don't know anyone in this city,
except you.

778
01:09:22,495 --> 01:09:23,895
And I have no money.

779
01:09:24,135 --> 01:09:26,695
Not a copeck, as it appears.

780
01:09:28,135 --> 01:09:30,134
And they won't sell me a ticket
without money.

781
01:09:34,014 --> 01:09:37,014
Could I borrow 15-16 Rubles from you?

782
01:09:37,254 --> 01:09:39,454
I'll send you the money
first thing tomorrow.

783
01:09:39,694 --> 01:09:41,694
Through wire transfer.

784
01:09:43,174 --> 01:09:46,973
Looks like I will have to pay you
to leave us alone.

785
01:09:47,213 --> 01:09:49,213
Please do.

786
01:09:49,453 --> 01:09:53,493
And now I ask you as a man:
What were you doing here?

787
01:09:53,733 --> 01:09:55,173
- Here?
- Yes, here.

788
01:09:55,413 --> 01:09:59,253
For God's sake, calm down.
I will explain everything.

789
01:09:59,533 --> 01:10:01,532
You see, we have this tradition.

790
01:10:01,773 --> 01:10:06,172
Every year on December 31 me
and my friends go to the bathhouse.

791
01:10:06,412 --> 01:10:10,292
We wash ourselves.
It's been many years now.

792
01:10:10,732 --> 01:10:15,371
After that Pavel was to go
to Leningrad.

793
01:10:15,612 --> 01:10:17,972
And I was planning
on getting married.

794
01:10:18,771 --> 01:10:19,771
To whom?

795
01:10:21,131 --> 01:10:22,451
To whom?

796
01:10:24,411 --> 01:10:26,891
That's not the point now.

797
01:10:27,130 --> 01:10:29,131
In the bathhouse we had a drink.

798
01:10:30,690 --> 01:10:32,970
To my fiancee, to me.

799
01:10:33,650 --> 01:10:34,931
Are you an alcoholic?

800
01:10:35,211 --> 01:10:37,210
No, I don't drink at all.

801
01:10:38,250 --> 01:10:42,810
I drink tea, coffee, liquid yogurt,..

802
01:10:43,049 --> 01:10:45,530
soft drinks, water...

803
01:10:46,649 --> 01:10:50,329
- Nadya? please.
- Don't overdo it!

804
01:10:50,569 --> 01:10:51,889
I am absolutely calm!

805
01:10:52,129 --> 01:10:56,969
After the bath
we went to the airport.

806
01:10:57,208 --> 01:11:01,169
Then we had some more to drink,
but that part I don't remember.

807
01:11:01,808 --> 01:11:07,568
I think they must have put me on
that plane instead of Pavel.

808
01:11:08,928 --> 01:11:10,648
I swear to God!

809
01:11:10,888 --> 01:11:14,128
- It's as simple as that.
- Yes. And very truthful.

810
01:11:14,447 --> 01:11:17,727
- What did you do in the plane?
- I flew.

811
01:11:17,968 --> 01:11:20,407
- Flew?
- Sleeping.

812
01:11:22,527 --> 01:11:24,127
I slept...

813
01:11:24,367 --> 01:11:27,967
Supposing you don't remember
how you got on that plane.

814
01:11:28,207 --> 01:11:31,246
But you have to remember
how you got out of it.

815
01:11:31,487 --> 01:11:34,566
Yes! I have to.

816
01:11:36,286 --> 01:11:37,766
But I don't.

817
01:11:39,006 --> 01:11:42,005
But I do remember
that I came here by cab.

818
01:11:42,325 --> 01:11:46,925
I said my home address,
and the driver brought me here.

819
01:11:47,925 --> 01:11:50,285
Supposing the key fit.

820
01:11:50,526 --> 01:11:51,725
Nadya, please...

821
01:11:52,445 --> 01:11:55,645
Supposing the key fit,
the address was the same,

822
01:11:55,885 --> 01:12:00,365
but you had to notice,
that the furniture was different!

823
01:12:00,645 --> 01:12:01,885
It's the same!

824
01:12:02,125 --> 01:12:06,564
But there's a mess here,
because the people have just moved in.

825
01:12:06,804 --> 01:12:10,444
We've also just moved in!
Me and my mother.

826
01:12:10,684 --> 01:12:14,844
That's enough!
Here's 15 Rubles, now leave.

827
01:12:15,084 --> 01:12:17,164
You don't know how grateful I am,
friends!

828
01:12:17,403 --> 01:12:20,323
You have to pay for your pleasures.

829
01:12:20,803 --> 01:12:24,843
I can't leave
without kissing you good-buy!

830
01:12:25,523 --> 01:12:28,043
You could have at least
waited until I leave.

831
01:12:28,282 --> 01:12:33,162
- Ippolit, wait!
- Who do you take me for, an idiot?

832
01:12:36,803 --> 01:12:37,802
Ippolit!

833
01:12:49,521 --> 01:12:51,721
- What did you tell him?
- The truth.

834
01:12:51,961 --> 01:12:53,441
What truth?

835
01:12:53,681 --> 01:12:58,401
Would you please help me
to my feet.

836
01:12:59,120 --> 01:13:02,360
I wore myself out with you folks.

837
01:13:02,800 --> 01:13:05,681
I told him, we go to this bathhouse.

838
01:13:05,920 --> 01:13:10,560
On December 31.
It's a tradition we have. We wash every year.

839
01:13:10,800 --> 01:13:14,680
That's exactly what I told him.

840
01:13:15,919 --> 01:13:21,160
Please don't cry.

841
01:13:21,559 --> 01:13:24,719
I'll go get him. Ippolit!

842
01:13:33,718 --> 01:13:36,158
Wait, don't leave!

843
01:13:37,518 --> 01:13:41,798
Ippolit! Sorry, I don't know
your patronymic.

844
01:13:42,438 --> 01:13:43,558
Wait!

845
01:13:43,798 --> 01:13:47,398
Don't leave! Wait!

846
01:13:48,797 --> 01:13:51,678
Don't bee a fool!

847
01:13:52,118 --> 01:13:55,517
Be a man, for Christ's sake!

848
01:14:27,555 --> 01:14:29,035
He left.

849
01:14:31,394 --> 01:14:33,874
He drives faster than I run.

850
01:14:34,794 --> 01:14:36,795
Here, take your 15 Rubles.

851
01:14:37,034 --> 01:14:39,634
Thank you,
I'll wire the money tomorrow.

852
01:14:39,874 --> 01:14:43,794
I hate you. You ruined my life.

853
01:14:44,714 --> 01:14:48,714
He will come back, believe me.
You'll see.

854
01:14:48,953 --> 01:14:51,954
The hot-tempered and the jealous
don't bear grudges for too long.

855
01:14:52,714 --> 01:14:54,953
If you only knew,
how well I understand you.

856
01:14:56,193 --> 01:14:58,193
My situation is even worse.

857
01:14:58,433 --> 01:15:01,793
A woman is waiting for me
in Moscow in an empty apartment.

858
01:15:02,792 --> 01:15:04,272
The woman I love.

859
01:15:05,353 --> 01:15:07,352
And here I am, in Leningrad.

860
01:15:07,672 --> 01:15:08,792
And?

861
01:15:09,112 --> 01:15:11,312
She doesn't know where you are?

862
01:15:11,552 --> 01:15:13,032
No, she must be hysterical.

863
01:15:13,272 --> 01:15:15,992
- Call her.
- I don't have a telephone card.

864
01:15:16,232 --> 01:15:19,551
Call credit. Through the operator.

865
01:15:20,871 --> 01:15:22,591
You are a sympathetic person.

866
01:15:22,912 --> 01:15:25,951
- Do you mind if I take my coat off?
- Whatever.

867
01:15:26,191 --> 01:15:27,431
Thank you.

868
01:15:35,790 --> 01:15:37,071
Operator!

869
01:15:37,351 --> 01:15:40,350
Happy New Year!

870
01:15:40,590 --> 01:15:42,110
I need to make a phone call.

871
01:15:42,350 --> 01:15:43,630
To Moscow.

872
01:15:44,190 --> 01:15:49,509
Number in Moscow? 454-60-21.

873
01:15:51,070 --> 01:15:54,229
Who will answer? Galya.

874
01:15:56,949 --> 01:15:59,549
That is, if she answers.

875
01:16:02,349 --> 01:16:04,349
In Leningrad? One moment please.

876
01:16:08,948 --> 01:16:10,348
Stay there!

877
01:16:10,588 --> 01:16:15,707
- What is your number?
- 14-50-30.

878
01:16:17,627 --> 01:16:20,907
Operator! 14-50-30.

879
01:16:25,427 --> 01:16:26,707
When?

880
01:16:28,707 --> 01:16:30,067
Can you make it faster?

881
01:16:47,586 --> 01:16:49,185
She said, within an hour.

882
01:16:51,506 --> 01:16:52,745
Oh, God...

883
01:16:53,706 --> 01:16:56,905
I'll wait on the landing, and you
will call me.

884
01:16:58,705 --> 01:17:03,145
Or you can explain everything
yourself.

885
01:17:03,425 --> 01:17:04,664
And I'll go.

886
01:17:04,905 --> 01:17:07,504
Oh no, you sort out your own
problems.

887
01:17:29,063 --> 01:17:31,782
2 minutes to go before the New
Year.

888
01:17:35,182 --> 01:17:37,183
Open the Champagne.

889
01:17:40,702 --> 01:17:42,862
It's in the fridge.

890
01:18:21,579 --> 01:18:24,739
No luck again. It's just not my day!

891
01:18:27,259 --> 01:18:28,699
I'm sorry.

892
01:18:36,419 --> 01:18:38,059
Happy New Year.

893
01:18:41,058 --> 01:18:42,538
What's your name?

894
01:18:44,698 --> 01:18:45,698
Nadya.

895
01:18:46,858 --> 01:18:48,538
I'm Zhenya.

896
01:18:49,098 --> 01:18:51,178
Happy New Year, Nadya.

897
01:18:53,017 --> 01:18:54,617
Same to you.

898
01:20:17,772 --> 01:20:20,132
What a good beginning of a new
year.

899
01:20:22,092 --> 01:20:23,412
Couldn't be better.

900
01:20:24,531 --> 01:20:25,771
That's true.

901
01:20:32,450 --> 01:20:34,090
There is an omen:

902
01:20:34,331 --> 01:20:38,331
You will live through the new year
the same way you see it in.

903
01:20:44,770 --> 01:20:46,770
What doctor are you?

904
01:20:48,210 --> 01:20:49,610
I'm a surgeon.

905
01:20:52,610 --> 01:20:53,610
And what are you?

906
01:20:54,769 --> 01:20:56,170
A teacher.

907
01:20:57,689 --> 01:20:59,769
I teach Russian and literature.

908
01:21:03,089 --> 01:21:05,089
Literature - that's wonderful.

909
01:21:07,888 --> 01:21:11,528
I have to find out, when's the first
flight to Moscow.

910
01:21:11,769 --> 01:21:16,208
- How do I do that? - There's a
telephone book over there.

911
01:21:34,007 --> 01:21:38,046
Hello? Operator? Happy New Year.

912
01:21:38,846 --> 01:21:42,606
When is the first flight to Moscow,
please?

913
01:21:46,486 --> 01:21:47,966
That's the first one?

914
01:21:53,685 --> 01:21:55,645
It's at 7 a. m.

915
01:22:00,085 --> 01:22:03,805
Nadya, don't worry. I'll leave as
soon as I talk to Galya.

916
01:22:04,284 --> 01:22:07,925
I'm beginning to think, you will
never leave here.

917
01:22:17,404 --> 01:22:20,084
Please don't worry.

918
01:22:21,843 --> 01:22:23,844
Everything will be fine.

919
01:22:24,404 --> 01:22:25,884
There's Moscow now!

920
01:22:26,123 --> 01:22:27,844
Moscow?!

921
01:22:35,443 --> 01:22:37,922
I think it was Ippolit.

922
01:22:38,202 --> 01:22:39,883
- Who?
- Ippolit.

923
01:22:41,762 --> 01:22:44,842
Why did you have to pick it up? Who
asked you to?

924
01:22:45,083 --> 01:22:48,242
How was I supposed to know? I
thought it was Moscow.

925
01:22:49,202 --> 01:22:51,202
I'm terribly sorry.

926
01:23:01,481 --> 01:23:03,161
Hello! Hello!

927
01:23:04,681 --> 01:23:05,681
Leningrad?

928
01:23:06,401 --> 01:23:08,041
I'll answer it!

929
01:23:14,680 --> 01:23:16,680
Hello? Yes, Moscow.

930
01:23:17,560 --> 01:23:19,520
Moscow? Hello!

931
01:23:19,879 --> 01:23:21,200
Would you please.

932
01:23:22,000 --> 01:23:24,519
- Galya, darling, it's me.
- You are in Leningrad?

933
01:23:27,159 --> 01:23:28,840
Thanks for calling anyway.

934
01:23:29,160 --> 01:23:31,479
Galya, Happy...

935
01:23:34,279 --> 01:23:36,118
Happy New Year.

936
01:23:36,718 --> 01:23:39,919
You called to wish me a Happy New
Year?

937
01:23:40,398 --> 01:23:42,999
- Not only that.
- I'm touched.

938
01:23:43,238 --> 01:23:45,238
I will explain everything.

939
01:23:45,478 --> 01:23:47,878
Wait till you hear this incredible
story.

940
01:23:48,118 --> 01:23:51,038
You won't believe it.

941
01:23:51,277 --> 01:23:54,677
I was so worried, I called all city
hospitals and morgues.

942
01:23:54,918 --> 01:23:56,917
And you simply ran away from me.

943
01:23:57,158 --> 01:23:58,918
I love you very much.

944
01:23:59,837 --> 01:24:02,797
Now I understand why you told me
about Leningrad.

945
01:24:03,037 --> 01:24:06,036
This is a different story.

946
01:24:06,277 --> 01:24:08,396
It has nothing to do with you.

947
01:24:08,637 --> 01:24:11,636
Every year on December 31 my
friends and I go to a bathhouse.

948
01:24:11,877 --> 01:24:13,716
It's an old tradition.

949
01:24:14,316 --> 01:24:17,316
There's nothing more to talk about.

950
01:24:17,556 --> 01:24:21,116
You can check. My number is
14-50-30.

951
01:24:21,355 --> 01:24:23,316
I'm taking the first flight to
Moscow.

952
01:24:23,555 --> 01:24:25,556
No need to be in a hurry.

953
01:24:26,596 --> 01:24:28,676
I'll leave the key on the table.

954
01:24:28,915 --> 01:24:32,795
No, please! Don't leave it!

955
01:25:17,312 --> 01:25:20,832
That's for me! Don't answer it!
Galya!

956
01:25:22,231 --> 01:25:24,352
3 minutes? Thank you.

957
01:25:31,671 --> 01:25:33,391
Well, that's it.

958
01:25:34,911 --> 01:25:36,871
I don't have a fiancee any more.

959
01:25:37,911 --> 01:25:40,670
No big deal, you'll find yourself
another one.

960
01:25:42,951 --> 01:25:46,910
Another one? What do you know
about it?

961
01:25:48,310 --> 01:25:51,750
All my life I've been looking for the
right woman.

962
01:25:53,830 --> 01:25:55,669
I was never married.

963
01:25:57,749 --> 01:25:59,589
And now finally when I found her...

964
01:26:01,429 --> 01:26:03,429
Why are you raising your voice at
me?

965
01:26:03,669 --> 01:26:06,428
I've had enough of your stupid
advice.

966
01:26:06,669 --> 01:26:08,788
Don't forget, you are at my place.

967
01:26:09,909 --> 01:26:12,388
The hell with your stupid apartment!

968
01:26:12,628 --> 01:26:14,509
Together with your stupid Otello!

969
01:26:14,748 --> 01:26:16,068
Impudent boor!

970
01:26:16,308 --> 01:26:17,508
You are a boor.

971
01:26:18,068 --> 01:26:19,668
Well if I am a boor, you are...

972
01:26:19,908 --> 01:26:23,588
What am I? Get out!

973
01:26:30,347 --> 01:26:33,507
I'm not going anywhere.

974
01:26:33,747 --> 01:26:36,227
- The flight is at 7 a.m.
- Then I will leave.

975
01:26:36,467 --> 01:26:39,427
Good riddance! I'm hungry as hell.

976
01:26:39,667 --> 01:26:43,227
- Oh no you don't!
- I'm hungry!

977
01:26:49,186 --> 01:26:51,106
You know, you're a genuine
termagant.

978
01:26:53,905 --> 01:26:58,306
One more word, and the next plate
will crash into your head.

979
01:27:07,545 --> 01:27:09,265
Your Galya left you.

980
01:27:12,904 --> 01:27:14,904
And she did the right thing.

981
01:27:18,544 --> 01:27:21,544
Now she will find a man worthy of
her.

982
01:27:32,063 --> 01:27:34,583
- What?
- What about?

983
01:27:34,823 --> 01:27:36,223
You don't object?

984
01:27:37,143 --> 01:27:38,943
Nothing you can say to that?

985
01:27:39,582 --> 01:27:43,462
No, it's just that I'm afraid of the
next plate.

986
01:27:43,702 --> 01:27:45,062
And you are right.

987
01:27:49,582 --> 01:27:51,502
That's Ippolit.

988
01:27:51,742 --> 01:27:53,382
Jump off the balcony.

989
01:27:53,622 --> 01:27:55,742
I'm not an idiot to fracture my legs.

990
01:27:59,462 --> 01:28:02,421
Happy New Year, Nadya!

991
01:28:02,941 --> 01:28:05,181
We were in the neighborhood and
decided to drop by.

992
01:28:06,141 --> 01:28:08,661
We left my husband downstairs.

993
01:28:08,901 --> 01:28:12,141
- He would sit for ages.
- It's not easy to get rid of a man.

994
01:28:12,381 --> 01:28:14,301
Where is he? Show us.

995
01:28:24,220 --> 01:28:26,019
There he is. In all his glory.

996
01:28:40,579 --> 01:28:41,579
Valya.

997
01:28:46,538 --> 01:28:47,778
Tanya.

998
01:28:50,378 --> 01:28:52,858
Dear Ippolit Georgievich!

999
01:28:54,017 --> 01:28:57,257
- We are Nadya's friends.
- We work in the same school.

1000
01:28:57,498 --> 01:29:00,178
She's been hiding you from us.

1001
01:29:00,417 --> 01:29:03,657
We came here to wish you
happiness.

1002
01:29:03,897 --> 01:29:09,577
We want you to know what a
wonderful person she is.

1003
01:29:10,696 --> 01:29:13,857
Everyone loves her: colleagues,
parents and even children.

1004
01:29:14,096 --> 01:29:15,296
She is sympathetic.

1005
01:29:15,536 --> 01:29:19,256
She is socially active and hangs in
the Hall of Fame.

1006
01:29:19,497 --> 01:29:20,736
I'm not the one...

1007
01:29:23,896 --> 01:29:26,816
Don't listen to him! Please sit down.

1008
01:29:27,055 --> 01:29:30,536
- Call your husband.
- We don't want to interfere!

1009
01:29:30,774 --> 01:29:33,936
There's nothing to interfere into. We
hardly know each other.

1010
01:29:34,175 --> 01:29:35,655
What's your patronymic?

1011
01:29:35,935 --> 01:29:37,415
Vasilyevna.

1012
01:29:39,655 --> 01:29:42,814
I've known Nadezhda Vasilyevna
since 11 p.m.

1013
01:29:43,055 --> 01:29:45,813
Ippolit, stop fooling around. That's
enough.

1014
01:29:46,054 --> 01:29:49,415
Let him make jokes. He's good at it.

1015
01:29:49,653 --> 01:29:51,054
But I am not Ipppolit.

1016
01:29:51,294 --> 01:29:54,054
I like your attitude to one another.

1017
01:29:54,292 --> 01:29:56,934
The attitude is rather complex.

1018
01:29:57,173 --> 01:30:00,973
You need a towel, it's going to shoot
out.

1019
01:30:01,213 --> 01:30:02,693
I will be careful.

1020
01:30:08,292 --> 01:30:11,973
Well, friends, here's to your happy
married life!

1021
