1412
02:02:41,640 --> 02:02:42,880
Nadya...

1413
02:02:45,600 --> 02:02:51,600
I want to ask you something...

1414
02:02:54,560 --> 02:02:58,280
A want to ask you a favor.
You may find it too daring...

1415
02:02:58,520 --> 02:02:59,840
But what is it?

1416
02:03:02,320 --> 02:03:05,280
You... won't be mad at me?

1417
02:03:06,640 --> 02:03:08,040
I'll try.

1418
02:03:08,560 --> 02:03:10,240
And you won't send me away?

1419
02:03:11,080 --> 02:03:13,640
Well, if I haven't done it so far...

1420
02:03:13,880 --> 02:03:16,720
- You want me to sing another song?
- No.

1421
02:03:22,120 --> 02:03:26,200
May I take out Ippolit's photograph

1422
02:03:26,440 --> 02:03:28,600
and tear it to pieces?

1423
02:03:30,160 --> 02:03:31,720
No, you may not.

1424
02:03:34,200 --> 02:03:36,440
Are you really
very unhappy that he left?

1425
02:03:39,640 --> 02:03:42,640
- Why do you need to know that?
- I have my reasons..

1426
02:03:45,520 --> 02:03:46,640
Yes, I am unhappy.

1427
02:03:47,640 --> 02:03:49,240
Are you sure?

1428
02:04:02,000 --> 02:04:05,880
How old are you? 32?

1429
02:04:07,480 --> 02:04:11,080
- Thirty three?
- Thirty four.

1430
02:04:11,280 --> 02:04:13,000
Thirty four?

1431
02:04:17,200 --> 02:04:19,480
And still no family.

1432
02:04:21,000 --> 02:04:22,880
No luck. That happens.

1433
02:04:24,360 --> 02:04:25,920
And suddenly there comes He.

1434
02:04:26,880 --> 02:04:28,200
All positive...

1435
02:04:29,720 --> 02:04:32,160
Serious and reliable.

1436
02:04:34,000 --> 02:04:35,200
Handsome.

1437
02:04:37,080 --> 02:04:38,040
Next to him you feel comfortable.

1438
02:04:38,600 --> 02:04:39,800
Protected.

1439
02:04:40,280 --> 02:04:42,400
As though behind a thick stone wall.

1440
02:04:43,000 --> 02:04:46,880
He's well off, and your friends
are giving their piece of advice:

1441
02:04:47,720 --> 02:04:49,360
"Don't let him get away!"

1442
02:04:50,600 --> 02:04:52,800
You can be cruel.

1443
02:04:54,760 --> 02:04:55,880
I'm sorry.

1444
02:05:01,000 --> 02:05:06,120
I'm a surgeon, there are times
when I have to cause people pain,

1445
02:05:06,360 --> 02:05:09,320
so that later on they would
be happy.

1446
02:05:10,320 --> 02:05:12,520
Do you ever feel sorry
for your patients?

1447
02:05:15,160 --> 02:05:16,360
Of course I do.

1448
02:05:18,880 --> 02:05:20,000
Yes...

1449
02:05:22,000 --> 02:05:24,360
Sometimes I feel sorry
for myself too.

1450
02:05:27,240 --> 02:05:28,560
I come home,..

1451
02:05:30,080 --> 02:05:33,320
sit in the armchair
and start feeling sorry for myself.

1452
02:05:36,560 --> 02:05:38,600
But that doesn't happen so often.

1453
02:05:41,160 --> 02:05:42,680
Have you ever been married?

1454
02:05:43,760 --> 02:05:46,200
I was. Half-married.

1455
02:05:47,640 --> 02:05:49,360
How's that? By what half?

1456
02:05:51,080 --> 02:05:55,480
That happens...
We met twice a week.

1457
02:05:57,880 --> 02:05:59,640
That went on for ten years.

1458
02:06:02,360 --> 02:06:05,760
And on weekends I was alone.

1459
02:06:08,760 --> 02:06:12,480
Since that time
I don't like weekends.

1460
02:06:13,480 --> 02:06:15,200
And I don't like holidays.

1461
02:06:18,840 --> 02:06:20,080
He was married?

1462
02:06:24,120 --> 02:06:25,680
He still is.

1463
02:06:28,600 --> 02:06:30,520
Do you still love him?

1464
02:06:34,120 --> 02:06:35,360
No.

1465
02:06:36,440 --> 02:06:37,680
No.

1466
02:06:38,600 --> 02:06:40,400
Let's go have some coffee.

1467
02:06:53,440 --> 02:06:56,440
You know,
I was never popular with women.

1468
02:06:57,040 --> 02:06:59,280
It started at school.
No, honestly.

1469
02:06:59,520 --> 02:07:03,520
There was this girl, Ira.
She was nothing special.

1470
02:07:03,760 --> 02:07:07,680
And as they say,
I had a crush on her.

1471
02:07:08,440 --> 02:07:11,520
And she didn't even notice me.

1472
02:07:11,760 --> 02:07:15,280
Then after we graduated,
she married Pavel.

1473
02:07:15,520 --> 02:07:17,440
The one you went
to the bathhouse with?

1474
02:07:17,680 --> 02:07:20,560
And instead of whom
you flew to Leningrad?

1475
02:07:20,800 --> 02:07:25,320
Yes. They got married
and invited me to their wedding.

1476
02:07:25,560 --> 02:07:28,120
I was very upset,
and I proposed a toast:

1477
02:07:28,360 --> 02:07:32,480
"Ira, I wish you to leave Pavel
and come to live with me"

1478
02:07:33,960 --> 02:07:36,200
They threw me out, of course.

1479
02:07:36,440 --> 02:07:40,960
- And now you are friends?
- We've been friends all our life.

1480
02:07:41,480 --> 02:07:44,040
It's not his fault
that she preferred him.

1481
02:07:45,080 --> 02:07:48,160
He was going to fly to Leningrad

1482
02:07:48,400 --> 02:07:50,240
to see in the New Year with her.

1483
02:07:53,200 --> 02:07:56,720
Poor Ira, another victim
of the situation.

1484
02:07:57,960 --> 02:07:59,440
Why "another"?

1485
02:08:00,760 --> 02:08:04,440
I don't consider myself a victim.

1486
02:08:10,840 --> 02:08:13,120
I'll go make some coffee,
and I'll do it with pleasure.

1487
02:08:13,360 --> 02:08:14,480
Why you?

1488
02:08:14,720 --> 02:08:18,680
Because you sing beautifully,
but you can't cook.

1489
02:08:18,920 --> 02:08:22,200
This is no fish in aspic,
it tastes more like strychnine.

1490
02:08:24,680 --> 02:08:27,840
- But you said you liked it.
- I was just toadying.

1491
02:08:28,280 --> 02:08:31,000
- You're not too polite.
- That's true.

1492
02:08:31,240 --> 02:08:34,320
I don't know what's gotten into me.
I've become so impudent.

1493
02:08:34,800 --> 02:08:38,360
All my life everyone
thought of me as bashful.

1494
02:08:38,600 --> 02:08:41,400
Everyone takes advantage of me.
My friends call me "softy".

1495
02:08:41,640 --> 02:08:43,720
They just wanted to flatter you.

1496
02:08:43,960 --> 02:08:46,760
No. I was of the same
opinion of myself

1497
02:08:47,000 --> 02:08:48,640
You were being overly modest.

1498
02:08:50,520 --> 02:08:52,080
And now I feel...

1499
02:08:53,280 --> 02:08:57,240
I'm becoming a different man.

1500
02:08:58,760 --> 02:09:00,840
- More impertinent?
- No, bold.

1501
02:09:01,080 --> 02:09:03,800
- More unmannerly?
- Firm.

1502
02:09:04,040 --> 02:09:05,760
- More impudent?
- Wrong again.

1503
02:09:07,840 --> 02:09:09,440
I feel that...

1504
02:09:12,840 --> 02:09:15,400
I can do anything.

1505
02:09:18,440 --> 02:09:20,280
as if some power inside me

1506
02:09:21,200 --> 02:09:25,360
was asleep, and now it's awakening.

1507
02:09:30,040 --> 02:09:33,200
Maybe it is because I met you?

1508
02:09:34,440 --> 02:09:35,920
Thanks to you?

1509
02:09:38,280 --> 02:09:40,600
Do you realize what you're saying?

1510
02:09:40,840 --> 02:09:42,880
That I made a boor out of you.

1511
02:09:44,960 --> 02:09:47,360
It is unheard of!

1512
02:09:48,640 --> 02:09:51,200
No one ever called me a boor.

1513
02:09:53,520 --> 02:09:55,000
Nadya, I'm happy.

1514
02:10:01,400 --> 02:10:04,320
How can one be so obtrusive!

1515
02:10:06,760 --> 02:10:09,160
I don't know what I'll do to him!

1516
02:10:09,400 --> 02:10:12,800
Don't... I'll open it.

1517
02:10:21,800 --> 02:10:25,640
- Nadya, what happened?
- You had a fight?

1518
02:10:26,280 --> 02:10:28,600
Was he rude to you, dear?

1519
02:10:28,840 --> 02:10:30,360
Did he hurt you?

1520
02:10:30,600 --> 02:10:33,400
And he produced
such a good impression at first!

1521
02:10:33,640 --> 02:10:36,080
Look at us, the old fools!
We swallowed his act.

1522
02:10:36,320 --> 02:10:38,880
- He's married!
- He has a child?

1523
02:10:39,120 --> 02:10:41,080
I'll explain everything.

1524
02:10:41,680 --> 02:10:44,360
What is this?
Who asked you to barge in here?

1525
02:10:44,600 --> 02:10:48,160
Go home, both of you!

1526
02:10:49,120 --> 02:10:50,360
Are you crazy?

1527
02:10:50,600 --> 02:10:52,400
She asked us to come.

1528
02:10:52,640 --> 02:10:55,920
- Nadya, let's go to my place.
- Give me the coat.

1529
02:10:56,160 --> 02:10:58,880
Give back the coat! It's not yours!

1530
02:10:59,200 --> 02:11:01,360
- She's not going anywhere!
- What a tone of voice!

1531
02:11:01,600 --> 02:11:04,480
- A normal tone.
- Why are you bossing around here?

1532
02:11:05,680 --> 02:11:07,160
Because I am Ippolit.

1533
02:11:10,600 --> 02:11:13,040
- What are you laughing at?
- You liar!

1534
02:11:14,440 --> 02:11:15,840
Girls, don't believe her.

1535
02:11:16,080 --> 02:11:18,320
- For the last time...
- Don't believe her.

1536
02:11:18,640 --> 02:11:20,880
- Go ahead, amuse yourself.
- He is not Ippolit.

1537
02:11:21,120 --> 02:11:23,360
He is a perfect stranger.

1538
02:11:24,760 --> 02:11:28,720
You don't believe she would
spend a night with a stranger?

1539
02:11:28,960 --> 02:11:31,680
- I come home...
- Tell them about the bathhouse.

1540
02:11:31,920 --> 02:11:36,520
- And see this...
- In your own bed!

1541
02:11:36,760 --> 02:11:41,000
- That's the interesting part.
- I think, we'd better go.

1542
02:11:41,240 --> 02:11:44,880
- Zhenya, stop this farce!
- What Zhenya? Where is he?

1543
02:11:45,120 --> 02:11:48,440
You brought Zhenya with you?!
I call a divorce!

1544
02:11:48,720 --> 02:11:50,440
- That's enough!
- Quiet, quiet!

1545
02:11:50,680 --> 02:11:54,520
You'll beet him up after we leave.
Go on.

1546
02:11:54,880 --> 02:11:55,960
He won't get away with this!

1547
02:11:56,200 --> 02:11:58,560
Girls, let's have a drink.

1548
02:11:58,800 --> 02:12:00,880
It's the New Year after all.

1549
02:12:02,920 --> 02:12:05,280
A toast to friendship!

1550
02:12:05,520 --> 02:12:08,400
Yes, let's drink to friendship.

1551
02:12:08,640 --> 02:12:11,520
This woman dragged me
along the floor all night.

1552
02:12:14,040 --> 02:12:15,720
Dear Nadya and Ippolit!

1553
02:12:15,960 --> 02:12:17,560
- He is not Ippolit.
- Come on!

1554
02:12:17,800 --> 02:12:20,360
Stop it. It's not funny any more!

1555
02:12:20,600 --> 02:12:23,240
- Here.
- I won't drink!

1556
02:12:23,840 --> 02:12:27,600
I wish you never ever
to fight in the new year.

1557
02:12:27,840 --> 02:12:28,960
We won't.

1558
02:12:29,200 --> 02:12:32,280
- Girls, I'm leaving with you.
- I've had enough!

1559
02:12:32,520 --> 02:12:34,000
Calm down, Ippolit.

1560
02:12:34,240 --> 02:12:36,800
Why aren't you asking us to kiss?

1561
02:12:37,360 --> 02:12:39,280
Give her a kiss! Give her a kiss!

1562
02:12:40,680 --> 02:12:42,480
I don't want to kiss this man!

1563
02:12:42,720 --> 02:12:46,560
It's not polite.
Why do you act stubborn?

1564
02:12:47,680 --> 02:12:49,880
The people are waiting!

1565
02:13:36,360 --> 02:13:37,840
Where are Tanya and Valya?

1566
02:13:41,280 --> 02:13:43,000
You have very good friends.

1567
02:13:45,040 --> 02:13:47,640
- When have you become so familiar?
- Long ago.

1568
02:13:50,080 --> 02:13:51,560
Haven't you noticed?

1569
02:13:59,680 --> 02:14:01,080
No peace in this house!..

1570
02:14:02,760 --> 02:14:04,720
People barging in all the time!

1571
02:14:05,200 --> 02:14:08,320
I swear I'll kill whoever it is!

1572
02:14:14,440 --> 02:14:16,160
Do the Sinitsyns live here?

1573
02:14:16,760 --> 02:14:17,960
What is your surname?

1574
02:14:18,440 --> 02:14:19,640
Sheveleva.

1575
02:14:20,680 --> 02:14:23,560
- We're the Shevelevs!
- Wrong address again!

1576
02:14:29,480 --> 02:14:31,600
- What is your surname?
- Lukashin.

1577
02:14:34,680 --> 02:14:36,560
- And the patronymic?
- Mikhailovich.

1578
02:14:37,880 --> 02:14:39,920
Yevgeny Mikhailovich Lukashin.

1579
02:14:41,320 --> 02:14:43,880
Nice to meet you.

1580
02:14:52,480 --> 02:14:54,600
- Where are you calling?
- The airport.

1581
02:14:55,880 --> 02:14:58,720
I want to ask when is
the second flight to Moscow.

1582
02:14:59,000 --> 02:15:00,960
You decided to postpone your trip?

1583
02:15:03,960 --> 02:15:05,560
I don't want to leave.

1584
02:15:05,800 --> 02:15:11,000
Hello! Operator,
when is the second flight to Moscow?

1585
02:15:14,600 --> 02:15:16,000
I see. And the third?

1586
02:15:18,280 --> 02:15:19,520
So soon?

1587
02:15:20,240 --> 02:15:21,520
And the fourth?

1588
02:15:22,960 --> 02:15:27,960
God dammit!
They leave every half an hour.

1589
02:15:32,640 --> 02:15:35,640
I don't understand,
why I have to leave.

1590
02:15:36,160 --> 02:15:37,560
What are you talking about?

1591
02:15:39,400 --> 02:15:40,840
I'm coming out
to work only on the 2nd.

1592
02:15:42,000 --> 02:15:44,400
We can walk around the city,

1593
02:15:45,240 --> 02:15:51,200
go to the Hermitage,
and in the evening I'll leave for Moscow.

1594
02:15:51,520 --> 02:15:52,760
By train.

1595
02:15:54,800 --> 02:15:56,880
You are being impudent again.

1596
02:15:58,480 --> 02:16:00,400
I didn't invite you to stay.

1597
02:16:02,080 --> 02:16:04,840
What's the problem?
Invite me.

1598
02:16:10,400 --> 02:16:11,640
What for?

1599
02:16:19,320 --> 02:16:23,280
I have a feeling
there's three of us here.

1600
02:16:23,600 --> 02:16:25,400
Don't touch him!.

1601
02:16:29,440 --> 02:16:33,080
I won't do anything to him,
just put him away between books.

1602
02:16:45,160 --> 02:16:48,280
All right, let him eavesdrop.
But let him look the other way.

1603
02:16:50,720 --> 02:16:52,400
I prefer not to see him.

1604
02:16:52,680 --> 02:16:53,920
Leave him alone!

1605
02:16:54,160 --> 02:16:57,760
You stand up for him
as if you cherished the memory of him.

1606
02:16:58,080 --> 02:16:59,320
That's none of your business.

1607
02:16:59,560 --> 02:17:02,120
"To my beloved Nadya"?

1608
02:17:05,240 --> 02:17:06,560
Well!

1609
02:17:06,800 --> 02:17:11,800
That is too much!

1610
02:17:16,480 --> 02:17:19,320
- What are you doing?
- Let him go get some fresh air!

1611
02:17:19,560 --> 02:17:21,000
It's good for his health.

1612
02:17:29,640 --> 02:17:32,520
- Go get Ippolit.
- Won't even think of doing it.

1613
02:17:32,760 --> 02:17:35,960
- I repeat.
- You don't have to!

1614
02:17:36,640 --> 02:17:39,280
- You'll take the first flight.
- I will do just that!

1615
02:17:39,520 --> 02:17:43,720
- Fly away!
- I will! I'll fly away!

1616
02:17:45,240 --> 02:17:48,600
Only I'll shave at first.

1617
02:17:49,720 --> 02:17:52,320
Shave with this shaver!
And then I'll fly away.

1618
02:17:53,440 --> 02:17:54,840
On an airplane...

1619
02:17:59,720 --> 02:18:01,720
This is not a hairdressing parlor.

1620
02:18:01,960 --> 02:18:04,440
Don't touch me! I'm unshaved.

1621
02:18:05,200 --> 02:18:07,760
I have to look neat
when I meet my fiancee.

1622
02:18:08,000 --> 02:18:12,680
I've forgotten
that you had a fiancee.

1623
02:18:16,240 --> 02:18:17,480
Go open the door!

1624
02:18:17,720 --> 02:18:21,120
It must be Ippolit.
It's been a while!

1625
02:18:38,160 --> 02:18:40,680
So now he's shaving
with my electric razor!

1626
02:18:56,920 --> 02:18:59,720
I hope this time he left for good.

1627
02:19:01,280 --> 02:19:02,760
Good riddance!

1628
02:19:03,840 --> 02:19:07,920
How come he keeps
his razor at your place?

1629
02:19:11,440 --> 02:19:13,760
You were going to your fiancee?
Well, good luck!

1630
02:19:14,640 --> 02:19:18,160
- This shaver belongs to my fiance.
- Your ex-fiance.

1631
02:19:18,400 --> 02:19:20,400
Ippolit is no longer here.
Vanished, gone for good.

1632
02:19:20,640 --> 02:19:23,240
Do you see him? Ippolit!
He's nowhere around!

1633
02:19:23,480 --> 02:19:26,920
If he shows up again,
I'll throw him down the stairwell!

1634
02:19:27,160 --> 02:19:29,160
Upside down.

1635
02:19:29,400 --> 02:19:32,720
What right have you got
to talk like that?

1636
02:19:33,520 --> 02:19:36,280
How come you interfere in my life?

1637
02:19:36,520 --> 02:19:38,560
You have to go to the airport.

1638
02:19:39,160 --> 02:19:43,320
My train is leaving late
in the evening.

1639
02:19:44,680 --> 02:19:48,000
Well!.. That's enough!

1640
02:19:49,280 --> 02:19:53,840
I'm hungry, and I'm thirsty.

1641
02:19:55,080 --> 02:19:56,720
I want to get some rest.

1642
02:19:57,400 --> 02:19:58,880
I'm tired.

1643
02:19:59,800 --> 02:20:03,360
- "A foggy morning"...
- Then I'll leave!

1644
02:20:03,920 --> 02:20:06,800
Good riddance!
"A foggy morning"...

1645
02:20:07,880 --> 02:20:11,440
"Good riddance"...

1646
02:20:12,520 --> 02:20:16,000
- I'll bring a policeman.
- I don't care if it's a squad.

1647
02:20:16,240 --> 02:20:20,520
"I don't care if its a firing squad

1648
02:20:25,720 --> 02:20:28,040
"Or a police detachment!"...

1649
02:20:33,320 --> 02:20:34,640
Give me my coat.

1650
02:20:35,560 --> 02:20:38,320
Me? With pleasure!

1651
02:20:48,000 --> 02:20:49,160
There you go.

1652
02:20:54,600 --> 02:20:56,160
- Not too tight?
- Zip them.

1653
02:20:56,920 --> 02:20:59,680
- What?
- Zip my boots for me.

1654
02:21:02,040 --> 02:21:03,280
With pleasure!

1655
02:21:04,800 --> 02:21:07,280
Thank you for the honor.

1656
02:21:11,840 --> 02:21:13,320
What is it?

1657
02:21:14,880 --> 02:21:16,680
Hold on, patient.

1658
02:21:17,840 --> 02:21:19,240
Now the other one.

1659
02:21:22,800 --> 02:21:27,880
I dreamed of this all my adult life.

1660
02:21:35,680 --> 02:21:40,400
Don't think of cleaning out the
apartment. I know your address.

1661
02:21:41,640 --> 02:21:43,640
Let go of me.

1662
02:23:01,560 --> 02:23:02,520
Taxi!

1663
02:23:17,880 --> 02:23:20,520
Next time go to a cab stop.

1664
02:23:21,040 --> 02:23:23,000
All right, where to?

1665
02:23:23,240 --> 02:23:26,760
- I haven't the slightest idea.
- Get out!

1666
02:23:27,080 --> 02:23:29,840
I think I have an idea.

1667
02:23:31,440 --> 02:23:33,760
To the Moscow railway station.

1668
02:24:03,360 --> 02:24:04,600
You free?

1669
02:24:26,360 --> 02:24:30,520
"Let's fill our glasses to the brim!"

1670
02:24:30,760 --> 02:24:32,560
"They lie, who..."

1671
02:24:41,400 --> 02:24:42,640
Who are you?

1672
02:24:45,320 --> 02:24:46,680
And who are you?

1673
02:24:48,080 --> 02:24:49,800
I think I know...

1674
02:24:50,600 --> 02:24:53,880
- I'm sorry...
- Don't come any closer, or I'll scream.

1675
02:24:54,560 --> 02:24:56,520
I will explain everything.

1676
02:24:56,760 --> 02:24:59,120
- Don't move!
- I'm not moving.

1677
02:24:59,360 --> 02:25:02,120
Don't be afraid of me.

1678
02:25:02,800 --> 02:25:05,040
What did you break
into our house for?

1679
02:25:05,840 --> 02:25:07,320
I'll try to explain.

1680
02:25:07,560 --> 02:25:10,400
Me and my friends
have this tradition.

1681
02:25:10,640 --> 02:25:14,880
In Moscow every year on
December 31 we go to a bathhouse.

1682
02:25:15,280 --> 02:25:18,560
Come on! Turn out your pockets!

1683
02:25:22,360 --> 02:25:24,600
I only stole 15 Rubles.

1684
02:25:24,840 --> 02:25:27,520
Not too much.
Put the money on the table.

1685
02:25:34,960 --> 02:25:36,440
Where are you?

1686
02:25:37,200 --> 02:25:38,680
Where have you vanished?

1687
02:25:40,520 --> 02:25:41,840
I got you!

1688
02:26:22,640 --> 02:26:23,880
One ticket to Moscow.

1689
02:26:24,120 --> 02:26:28,080
I asked the ash-tree:

1690
02:26:28,320 --> 02:26:32,000
Where is my loved one?

1691
02:26:33,600 --> 02:26:36,480
The ash-tree didn't answer me,

1692
02:26:37,280 --> 02:26:40,320
It just shook its head.

1693
02:26:41,960 --> 02:26:45,120
I asked the poplar:

1694
02:26:46,080 --> 02:26:49,760
Where is my loved one?

1695
02:26:50,880 --> 02:26:54,360
The poplar threw its autumn leaves

1696
02:26:54,920 --> 02:26:58,560
All over me.

1697
02:26:59,640 --> 02:27:03,080
I asked autumn:

1698
02:27:03,960 --> 02:27:07,400
Where is my loved one?

1699
02:27:09,120 --> 02:27:11,720
Autumn answered

1700
02:27:13,880 --> 02:27:16,120
With a pouring rain.

1701
02:27:18,120 --> 02:27:21,120
I asked the rain:

1702
02:27:21,640 --> 02:27:25,240
Where is my loved one?

1703
02:27:26,360 --> 02:27:30,440
The rain shed its tears

1704
02:27:31,440 --> 02:27:35,200
Outside my window.

1705
02:27:35,760 --> 02:27:39,240
I asked the half-moon:

1706
02:27:40,200 --> 02:27:44,080
Where is my loved one?

1707
02:27:45,280 --> 02:27:48,200
The half-moon hid behind a
cloud

1708
02:27:50,320 --> 02:27:52,600
And didn't answer me..

1709
02:27:53,560 --> 02:27:57,280
I asked the cloud:

1710
02:27:58,040 --> 02:28:01,520
Where is my loved one?

1711
02:28:02,880 --> 02:28:06,400
The cloud disappeared

1712
02:28:07,080 --> 02:28:10,240
In the blue of the sky.

1713
02:28:12,320 --> 02:28:15,800
My only true friend,

1714
02:28:16,560 --> 02:28:19,720
Where is my loved one?

1715
02:28:21,760 --> 02:28:24,440
Tell me where she went.

1716
02:28:25,480 --> 02:28:28,080
Do you know where she is?

1717
02:28:29,600 --> 02:28:33,600
My only friend,

1718
02:28:34,320 --> 02:28:38,000
My only true friend answered me:

1719
02:28:38,560 --> 02:28:42,080
She who was your loved one,

1720
02:28:43,600 --> 02:28:46,640
She who was your loved one,

1721
02:28:47,680 --> 02:28:51,120
She who was your loved one,

1722
02:28:51,920 --> 02:28:55,160
Is now my wife.

1723
02:29:06,120 --> 02:29:09,080
I asked the ash-tree...

1724
02:29:10,280 --> 02:29:13,720
I asked autumn...

1725
02:29:14,880 --> 02:29:17,840
I asked the poplar...

1726
02:29:24,120 --> 02:29:27,080
Mother!
Why are you sitting in the hall?

1727
02:29:27,320 --> 02:29:30,960
I'm guarding a thief,
and he entertains me with his songs.

1728
02:29:31,200 --> 02:29:32,520
The thief is me.

1729
02:29:32,760 --> 02:29:34,880
Happy New Year, Nadya.

1730
02:29:37,280 --> 02:29:39,840
Mother, let's set him free.

1731
02:29:42,200 --> 02:29:44,920
You're cold?

1732
02:29:45,480 --> 02:29:47,960
No, I took a taxi.

1733
02:29:48,200 --> 02:29:50,560
Where is it you went by taxi?

1734
02:29:51,040 --> 02:29:55,480
I bought you a ticket
on the morning train.

1735
02:29:58,120 --> 02:30:00,120
You bought me a ticket?

1736
02:30:01,160 --> 02:30:05,080
Thank you. I'm much obliged.

1737
02:30:05,800 --> 02:30:07,280
The lower berth!

1738
02:30:08,120 --> 02:30:10,600
I don't know how to thank you!

1739
02:30:12,040 --> 02:30:15,600
Now I won't have to stand in line.

1740
02:30:15,840 --> 02:30:17,040
Thank you.

1741
02:30:18,640 --> 02:30:19,880
Thank you.

1742
02:30:22,120 --> 02:30:25,000
Even though
I don't have a very big salary...

1743
02:30:33,240 --> 02:30:36,320
I think I'll go to Lyuba's
to continue to celebrate.

1744
02:30:36,560 --> 02:30:40,080
Thank you, you're a terrific mother.

1745
02:30:45,560 --> 02:30:47,920
Nadya, I hope when I return

1746
02:30:48,200 --> 02:30:50,200
there won't be another stranger here.

1747
02:30:50,480 --> 02:30:53,080
Don't worry, I'll see to that.

1748
02:31:00,400 --> 02:31:02,520
Remember, I promised you

1749
02:31:02,800 --> 02:31:05,240
I would return
with the photograph of Ippolit?

1750
02:31:11,880 --> 02:31:14,320
- Oh, how terrible!
- You're an adventurer!

1751
02:31:14,600 --> 02:31:17,120
- What a pity!
- You're an insolent man!

1752
02:31:17,360 --> 02:31:19,480
Jesus, what small pieces!

1753
02:31:20,720 --> 02:31:22,920
- You're a shameless boor!
- Of course.

1754
02:31:23,160 --> 02:31:24,680
- A gangster!
- Of course.

1755
02:31:24,920 --> 02:31:26,280
- A barbarian!
- Of course.

1756
02:31:27,280 --> 02:31:30,480
- An alcoholic.
- Of course.

1757
02:31:32,480 --> 02:31:34,280
- A lump.
- Yes, yes.

1758
02:31:34,720 --> 02:31:36,440
You know who you are?..

1759
02:31:49,600 --> 02:31:51,080
Let's not open it.

1760
02:31:52,880 --> 02:31:54,360
We're not in.

1761
02:31:59,480 --> 02:32:02,960
Whoever it is,
let's not open the door.

1762
02:32:05,400 --> 02:32:06,880
Strange people.

1763
02:32:08,240 --> 02:32:10,800
If we don't open,
that means we're not in.

1764
02:32:12,000 --> 02:32:14,160
And if we're in but we don't open it,

1765
02:32:15,880 --> 02:32:18,640
that means we don't want
to see anyone.

1766
02:32:24,320 --> 02:32:25,800
How tactless!

1767
02:32:27,160 --> 02:32:29,040
How unmannered!

1768
02:32:33,000 --> 02:32:36,280
That's too much!

